sentences: Jeff Plate (born March 26, 1962) is an American professional hard rock/heavy metal drummer.

He is best known as drummer for American heavy metal band Savatage on their albums since Japan Live '94, and was also a member of Metal Church from 2006 to their break up in 2009 and again from their reunion in 2012 to 2017.

Jeff moved to Tampa, Florida in 1981, but soon returned New York, before moving once again to the Boston area.
In the fall of 1992, Zak got the call to join Savatage, replacing recently departed Jon Oliva.
Zak accepted and made his Savatage debut on 1993's Edge of Thorns.
In 1993, Plate moved back to upstate New York to regroup, joining an alternative/country rock band called Voodoo Rodeo.
Although the band has not performed since 2012, there has been no official statement on the band's breakup.
In 2006 Plate recorded "Long Time No Sing"  with vocalist John West.
Plate joined American heavy metal band Metal Church in 2006.
After some member changes and a brief hiatus, they reformed in 2012 and released two more albums (Generation Nothing and XI) before Plate left the band in March 2017.

In 2009, Jeff would team up once more with former Savatage bandmate Zak Stevens and former Wicked Witch bandmate Matt Leff to relaunch Wicked Witch under a new moniker, Machines of Grace.
Jeff's sister Terry died in a car accident in 2003, an event Jeff said "changed my lifeâ€¦"  Terry is survived by her 2 sons Bradley and Jeff.
In 2008 Plate married Cathy Fracasso.
In 2020, Jeff Plate announced the formation of a new project he was starting called 'Alta Reign'.

The group released their debut record in early 2021 to much success and plenty of positive reviews, The group is currently in the midst of recording their second album, due for release sometime in 2022.

He is best known as drummer for American heavy metal band Savatage on their albums since Japan Live '94, and was also a member of Metal Church from 2006 to their break up in 2009 and again from their reunion in 2012 to 2017.
Plate was born in Montour Falls, New York, and grew up on a farm in Horseheads, New York.
On crutches for 4 months, he was advised to give up playing sports for two years so the hip could heal properly.
After watching Kiss perform on The Midnight Special, he began taking drum lessons in school and privately.
In the fall of 1992, Zak got the call to join Savatage, replacing recently departed Jon Oliva.
Replacing drummer Andy James, he joined the band for the 'Handful Of Rain' U. S tour in the fall of '94.
Plate recorded three more albums with Savatage - "Dead Winter Dead", "The Wake Of Magellan", and "Poets and Madmen".
The success of the single "Christmas Eve/Sarajevo 12/24" from Dead Winter Dead lead to the formation of the Trans-Siberian Orchestra (TSO).

Plate has performed on every TSO release to date, including "Christmas Eve and Other Stories", "The Christmas Attic", "Beethoven's Last Night", "The Lost Christmas Eve", "Nightcastle" and the EP "Dreams of Fireflies (On a Christmas Night)".
He has performed on every Trans-Siberian Orchestra Tour, including the annual Winter Tours and several Spring Tours.
Jeff currently resides in upstate New York and, when not touring with TSO, gives private drum lessons.

The group released their debut record in early 2021 to much success and plenty of positive reviews, The group is currently in the midst of recording their second album, due for release sometime in 2022.
